.TH PK 1 "2026-02-28" "0.1.0-dev" "Peek (pk) User Manual"
.SH NAME
pk \- a minimalist, high-performance directory browser
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pk
[\fIPATH\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pk
is a zero-dependency utility written in x86_64 assembly. It lists directory 
contents by communicating directly with the Linux kernel via the getdents64 
system call.
.PP
It is designed to be orders of magnitude smaller than the standard GNU ls.
.SH OPTIONS
Currently, pk accepts a single optional argument:
.TP
.I PATH
The directory to list. If omitted, pk defaults to the current directory (.).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
General error (e.g., directory not found or permission denied).
